	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=147230"><span id=" ">Castanada</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">11 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>As posted and as confirmed via parsing, you may only proc once per 'melee action'.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not only can you proc when you actually *hit* something, but also when you miss (and as far as I know even on a riposte hit/miss).<br/><br/>Most people have their misses turned off, so it *could* appear as if you proc'd twice on the same 'hit', when in fact you swung twice, only 'hit' with one, but proc with both.  Again, if this can happen on riposte, this would be even more frequent.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
